 The career risk for LP22 is working below their actual level. This happens not from lack of ambition but from self-doubt, practical constraints, or difficulty finding work at their scale. The period of conventional career-building that precedes larger work feels deeply frustrating. It's worth sitting with.
 </p>
 <p>
 What LP22 needs from a career: genuine scale, latitude to think and plan at a large horizon, and the sense that what they're building matters. Work that is well-paid but small eventually produces restlessness no amount of success can address.
